msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/magma_mephit.md:11
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Armor Class** 11    \n"
"**Hit Points** 22 (5d6 + 5)    \n"
"**Speed** 30 ft., fly 30 ft. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/magma_mephit.md:15
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| STR     | DEX     | CON     | INT     | WIS     | CHA     |\n"
"|---------|---------|---------|---------|---------|---------|\n"
"| 8 (−1)  | 12 (+1) | 12 (+1) | 7 (−2)  | 10 (+0) | 10 (+0) |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/magma_mephit.md:23
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Skills** Stealth +3    \n"
"**Damage Vulnerabilities.** cold    \n"
"**Damage Immunities** fire, poison    \n"
"**Condition Immunities** poisoned    \n"
"**Senses** darkvision 60 ft., passive Perception 10    \n"
"**Languages** Ignan, Terran    \n"
"**Challenge** 1/2 (100 XP) \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/magma_mephit.md:27
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Death Burst.** When the mephit dies, it explodes in a burst of lava. Each "
"creature within 5 feet of it must make a DC 11 Dexterity saving throw, "
"taking 7 (2d6) fire damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a "
"successful one.    \n"
"**False Appearance.** While the mephit remains motionless, it is "
"indistinguishable from an ordinary mound of magma.    \n"
"**Innate Spellcasting (1/Day).** The mephit can innately cast **_heat "
"metal_** (spell save DC 10), requiring no material components. Its innate "
"spellcasting ability is Charisma. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/magma_mephit.md:30
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"### Actions    \n"
"**Claws.** _Melee Weapon Attack:_ +3 to hit, reach 5 ft., one "
"creature. _Hit:_ 3 (1d4 + 1) slashing damage plus 2 (1d4) fire damage.    \n"
"**Fire Breath (Recharge 6).** The mephit exhales a 15-foot cone of "
"fire. Each creature in that area must make a DC 11 Dexterity saving throw, "
"taking 7 (2d6) fire damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a "
"successful one.\n"
msgstr ""
